comments: O'Neale (UTA) lowers his shoulder and delivers contact to Poeltl's (SAS) side as Poeltl sets the pick.
Gobert (UTA) grasps and then quickly releases Johnson's (SAS) jersey during rebounding.

Johnson (SAS) extends his arm in pursuit of the rebound and marginal contact occurs with the side of Gobert's (UTA) head as Gobert retrieves the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Walker IV (SAS) steps into Mitchell's (UTA) path to the basket and initiates contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Poeltl (SAS) extends his left arm outward and initiates contact with Gobert's (UTA) head and arm, affecting Gobert's ability to rebound the ball.
Conley (UTA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Murray (SAS) prior to any incidental arm contact occurring.
Conley (UTA) maintains a rested forearm on Walker IV's (SAS) back and marginal contact occurs after Walker IV secures the loose ball.
Poeltl (SAS) firms up in his screening position in House Jr.'s (UTA) path and does not deliver the contact.
House Jr. (UTA) initiates contact with Walker IV's (SAS) right elbow and affects his jump shot attempt.
Poeltl (SAS) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Gobert (UTA) prior to any incidental contact occurring during rebounding.
Gobert (UTA) grabs and pulls Poeltl's (SAS) shorts during the rebound.
Gobert (UTA) brushes Poeltl's (SAS) right arm and marginal contact occurs prior to Gobert blocking the layup attempt.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Murray's (SAS) path and does not deliver the contact.
Poeltl (SAS) and Gobert (UTA) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Poeltl (SAS) brings his hands outward toward O'Neale;s (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs as Poeltl releases away to roll.
Mitchell (UTA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Johnson (SAS) prior to incidental arm and body contact taking place.
Gobert (UTA) jumps vertically and absorbs the body contact that occurs as Poeltl (SAS) drifts forward during the follow-through of his floater attempt.
Murray (SAS) and Mitchell (UTA) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Murray (SAS) stops his forward momentum and is retreating away from Mitchell (UTA) as he absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs during the pass.

Poeltl (SAS) has a grasp of Gobert's (UTA) left arm and marginal contact occurs as they each elevate to pursue the rebound. After Poeltl back-taps the ball, his left hand moves outward and marginal contact occurs with Gobert's face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Johnson (SAS) is moving forward when marginal body contact occurs with Mitchell's (UTA) left side as Mitchell retrieves the rebound.

Johnson (SAS) legally contests Mitchell's (UTA) jump shot attempt and would avoid Mitchell's right leg if he did not extend it forward to initiate the marginal contact. After communicating with the Replay Center, the on-court ruling of a two point basket was confirmed.
House Jr. (UTA) commits a take foul on Richardson (SAS).

Johnson (SAS) and O'Neale (UTA) engage and disengage with one another as they attempt to establish rebounding position. As they elevate in pursuit of the ball, Johnson and O'Neale make incidental body and arm contact with one another.
O'Neale (UTA) commits a take foul on Johnson (SAS).
Murray (SAS) and Conley (UTA) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Conley (UTA) commits a take foul on Murray (SAS).
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Gay's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Murray (SAS) and Mitchell (UTA) make incidental knee-to-knee contact with one another during the inbound.
Gay (UTA) commits a take foul on Murray (SAS).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Gay (UTA) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
